						<summary>

						<p>This undated inscription refers itself to the reign of the Noḻamba-Pallava king <hi rend="bold">Noḻambādhirāja.</hi> It was set up in memory of the death of a hunting dog, named <hi rend="bold">Pūṇiga,</hi> after killing a wild boar. Some chief (name lost) is said to have been ruling over <hi rend="bold">Taṇṇūru</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Chōragiri.</hi></p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
